12/07/2005
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Police announced on Monday (11 July) that they have increased security measures in Istanbul and other locations, following last week's bombings in London. 
They said there was information suggesting that a female suicide bomber would attempt to attack one of the largest towns. 
A blast at a resort in Cesme on Sunday injured 20 people.
In other news, officials said Tuesday that Kurdish terrorists kidnapped a Turkish soldier after robbing dozens of vehicles at a temporary roadblock in eastern Turkey. 
There has been a sharp rise in militant activity in southeast Turkey recently. 
(BBC - 12/07/05; Reuters, AFP - 11/07/05)
